    40	/*
    41	 *  NR SLOT PROCESSING SEQUENCE
    42	 *
    43	 *  Processing occurs with following steps for connected mode:
    44	 *
    45	 *  - Rx samples for a slot are received,
    46	 *  - PDCCH processing (including DCI extraction for downlink and uplink),
    47	 *  - PDSCH processing (including transport blocks decoding),
    48	 *  - PUCCH/PUSCH (transmission of acknowledgements, CSI, ... or data).
    49	 *
    50	 *  Time between reception of the slot and related transmission depends on UE processing performance.
    51	 *  It is defined by the value NR_UE_CAPABILITY_SLOT_RX_TO_TX.
    52	 *
    53	 *  In NR, network gives the duration between Rx slot and Tx slot in the DCI:
    54	 *  - for reception of a PDSCH and its associated acknowledgment slot (with a PUCCH or a PUSCH),
    55	 *  - for reception of an uplink grant and its associated PUSCH slot.
    56	 *
    57	 *  So duration between reception and it associated transmission depends on its transmission slot given in the DCI.
    58	 *  NR_UE_CAPABILITY_SLOT_RX_TO_TX means the minimum duration but higher duration can be given by the network because UE can support it.
    59	 *
    60	 *                                                                                                    Slot k
    61	 *                                                                                  -------+------------+--------
    62	 *                Frame                                                                    | Tx samples |
    63	 *                Subframe                                                                 |   buffer   |
    64	 *                Slot n                                                            -------+------------+--------
    65	 *       ------ +------------+--------                                                     |
    66	 *              | Rx samples |                                                             |
    67	 *              |   buffer   |                                
